==English==
===Noun===
'''[[bottom]] [[line]]'''
#(''accounting'') The final [[balance]]; the amount of [[money]] or [[profit]] left after everything has been tallied.
#{{idiom}} The [[summary]] or [[result]]; the most important information; the [[upshot]].
#:''The '''bottom line''' is that there simply are not enough hours in the day to finish all there is to do.''

Bottom Line refers to the bottom line of an Income Statement. The bottom line shows the Net Income Available To Shareholders. 

e.g.When a company talks about increasing the bottom line, they mean doing things to either increase the revenue or decrease expenses so the company's income increases.